{# Macro: testing_compliance_gates_summary

   Purpose: Compact summary of testing compliance gates for inline use in skills.
            Update here when gates are added/removed/reworded in testing.md.j2.
            Canonical definitions live in rules/testing.md.j2 — this is the compact form.

   Example:
     {{ testing_compliance_gates_summary() }}
#}
{% macro testing_compliance_gates_summary() -%}
- CG-1: Real behaviour assertions — no mock existence or placeholders
- CG-2: No test-only methods in production — utilities in repo-specific locations per architecture.md §7.3
- CG-3: Mocks at IO/network level only — never mock business logic test depends on
- CG-4: Mock mirrors complete real API structure — all documented fields
- CG-5: Test isolation — self-contained, no shared state, order-independent
- CG-6: Coverage scope — happy path, error paths, boundary conditions
- CG-7: Shared test data uses factories or helpers — no duplicated inline construction across files
{%- endmacro %}

{# Macro: conditional_security_reads

   Purpose: Generates read instructions for security-specific files based on capability flags.
            Routes to instructions/ for explicit config, rules/security/ for auto-detected domains.
            Auto-detects applicable security domains from capability combinations when security_dict empty.

   Parameters:
     - caps: The capabilities dict from context (required)
     - security_dict: The security namespace/dict from context (optional, default: {})

   Routing:
     - If security_dict populated: reads from /midtempo-framework/instructions/{page} (bespoke, persistent)
     - If security_dict empty: reads from /midtempo-framework/rules/security/{domain}.md (regenerated)

   Example:
     {{ conditional_security_reads(capabilities, security) }}

   Output (auto-detected):
     VERIFY-COMPLETE-READ for EVERY file below:
       CHECK the last line says "END OF DOCUMENT"
       IF CHECK fails → Re-read from offset until true end

     IF the current task involves secrets management
     READ ALL of `/midtempo-framework/rules/security/secrets-management.md` → for secrets-management rules

   Output (explicit config):
     VERIFY-COMPLETE-READ for EVERY file below:
       [...]
     IF the current task involves secrets management
     READ ALL of `/midtempo-framework/instructions/secrets-management.md` → for secrets-management rules
#}
{% macro conditional_security_reads(caps, security_dict={}) -%}
{{ verify_complete_read_header() }}
{% set auto_domains = ['secrets-management'] %}
{% if caps.hasUI or caps.hasDB %}
  {% set _ = auto_domains.append('input-validation') %}
{% endif %}
{% if caps.hasAuthentication %}
  {% set _ = auto_domains.append('authentication') %}
{% endif %}
{% if caps.handlesConfidentialData %}
  {% set _ = auto_domains.append('data-protection') %}
{% endif %}
{% if caps.isPublicFacing %}
  {% set _ = auto_domains.append('public-hardening') %}
{% endif %}
{% set final_domains = security_dict.keys() | list if security_dict else auto_domains %}
{% set path_prefix = '/midtempo-framework/instructions/' if security_dict else '/midtempo-framework/rules/security/' %}
{% for domain in final_domains %}
{% set page = security_dict[domain].page if security_dict and domain in security_dict else (domain ~ '.md') %}
{% if domain == 'secrets-management' -%}
IF the current task involves secrets management
{% elif domain == 'input-validation' -%}
IF the current task involves input validation
{% elif domain == 'authentication' -%}
IF the current task involves authentication
{% elif domain == 'data-protection' -%}
IF the current task involves data protection
{% elif domain == 'public-hardening' -%}
IF the current task involves public-facing security
{% endif -%}
{{ read_file(path_prefix ~ page, 'for ' ~ domain ~ ' rules') -}}
{{ '\n' if not loop.last }}
{% endfor %}
{%- endmacro %}

